1. Amount owed to the entity for goods or services sold or provided on credit (typically "Accounts Receivable").
2. Amounts owed by the entity for goods or services received or purchased on credit (typically "Accounts Payable").

We then extract the initial and end values for both line items.

| Accounts Payable   | 0.00           | 2023-12-31   | 462000.00   | 2024-02-05 |

---

- end valu1 (Accounts Receivable) = 2902136.39
